[MOVEMENT & ANIMATION RELATED] (Green) - Extension Features
-------------------------------------------------------------
1. No Animation / Cartman Walk
   - Description: Forces the character into a broken idle/T-Pose state so they glide across the floor without moving their legs.
   - Target AOB Signature: F3 0F 11 86 ?? ?? ?? ?? 0F 57 (Example: Animation speed/blend write)
   - Method: Hook the animation speed float. Force the value to 0.0 to freeze the current frame, or force the Animation State ID to 0.
   - Key Offsets (Typical for this engine):
     -> +0120 = Animation State ID (4 Bytes) [Force to 0 for T-Pose/Glide]
     -> +0128 = Animation Playback Speed (Float) [Force to 0 to freeze anim]

2. Walk Through Walls (Disable Collision)
   - Description: Tricks the game into thinking the player is airborne, disabling horizontal collision.
   - Target AOB Signature: 88 81 ?? ?? ?? ?? 0F B6 D0 (Example: IsGrounded boolean write)
   - Method: Find the "IsGrounded" or "CollisionEnabled" boolean. Hook the write instruction and force the value to 0.
   - Key Offsets (Typical for this engine):
     -> +01E0 = Is Grounded Flag (1 Byte) [Force to 0 to walk through walls]
     -> +01E4 = Collision Enabled Flag (1 Byte) [Force to 0]

3. Noclip (Free Movement)
   - Description: Disables collision completely and allows free flight using camera coordinates.
   - Target AOB Signature: F3 0F 11 ?? ?? ?? ?? ?? F3 0F 11 (Example: Coordinate X/Y/Z write)
   - Method: Hook the coordinate writes. Use Auto Assembler to inject a script that adds/subtracts from X/Y/Z based on keypresses (e.g., Arrow keys or W/S) while collision is disabled.
   - Key Offsets (Typical for this engine):
     -> +0050 = Coordinate X (Float)
     -> +0054 = Coordinate Y (Float)
     -> +0058 = Coordinate Z (Float)
     -> +0060 = Rotation / Camera Angle (Float) [Used to calculate forward movement vector]


